# Picker Frontend Rules

## Naming
- Prefer single-word base form; verbs for functions, singular nouns for data.
- Avoid abbreviations unless widely accepted (e.g., auth, api, ui).
- Collections: use singular name + _list/_map (e.g., course_list).

## Style
- TypeScript-only, use explicit types for public APIs and props.
- English-only code, comments, docs, commits.
- Code comments must be written in English only.
- Keep files small and focused; one component per file.

## Conventions
- Follow Google JavaScript Style Guide for TypeScript/JS.
- Follow Only No CSS principles: no custom CSS usage.

## HTML Authoring
- Use semantic HTML tags whenever possible.
- Do not use `div` or `span`.
- Prefer sectioning tags (`header`, `main`, `section`, `article`, `footer`) for layout.

## Architecture
- Fresh: keep routes thin; place UI logic in components or islands.
- Islands: only for interactivity; avoid unnecessary client JS.
- Shared UI goes in `components/`, interactive pieces in `islands/`.

## Data & API
- Centralize API calls in `lib/api/` and reuse typed clients.
- Validate and normalize external data at the boundary.
- Prefer `fetch` wrappers with typed response parsing.

## State & Effects
- Use `@preact/signals` for local UI state.
- Avoid global state unless required; document cross-route state.
- Handle async errors explicitly; surface user-friendly messages.

## WharfKit
- Load WharfKit only inside islands.
- Keep chain config in a single module (e.g., `lib/wharfkit/`).
- Never log or persist sensitive wallet data.

## CSS
- Do not use CSS files, inline styles, or style attributes.
- Do not use CSS frameworks (including Tailwind).
- Avoid class-based styling; rely on semantic HTML structure only.

## HTML Tags (Allowed)
- Use only the 118 HTML5 tags listed below.
- Note: Preact-friendly UI tags (e.g., dialog, details, summary, menu, canvas,
  svg, progress, meter, output, datalist, template, slot) are included in the
  list below; use them freely.
- html, head, body, title, meta, link, base
- header, footer, main, nav, aside, section, article, h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6, hgroup, address
- p, hr, pre, blockquote, ol, ul, li, dl, dt, dd, figure, figcaption, div
- a, em, strong, small, s, cite, q, dfn, abbr, ruby, rt, rp, data, time, code, var, samp, kbd, sub, sup, i, b, u, mark, bdi, bdo, span, br, wbr
- img, iframe, embed, object, picture, source, video, audio, track, map, area
- table, caption, colgroup, col, tbody, thead, tfoot, tr, td, th
- form, label, input, button, select, datalist, optgroup, option, textarea, output, progress, meter, fieldset, legend, details, summary, dialog, search
- script, noscript, template, slot, canvas, svg, math
- ins, del, menu

